<h2 id="section-top">Physiotherapy</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=633">Chesterfield Royal Hospital NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address">Physiotherapy/Occupational Therapy<br/>01246 512173</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContentd6c7b7f0bb7e44a78220a3dad64af04f">
</div>
<p><strong>Physiotherapy</strong> – provides a range of in and out patient services to the Trust, for adults and children (excluding children with developmental delay).  The aim of Physiotherapy following an individual assessment is to maintain or restore optimal function to patients enabling them to lead as high a quality of life as possible.  The majority of the out patient work, for GP and Consultant referred patients, is for patients who have musculoskeletal, respiratory, neurological, rheumatological or Women’s Health conditions.  All Physiotherapists are Health Profession Council and Chartered Society of Physiotherapy registered.   Staff undertake specialist training to provide the most up to date evidence based treatment e.g.</p>
<p>The  MSK department has Senior staff who have undertaken a range of post graduate specialist training in e.g  diagnosing and treating neck, back and shoulder problems; hand, lower limb and sport injuries.  Our musculo-skeletal (MSK)  Out patient services can be accessed via Choose and Book as well as following a visit to your GP surgery. Urgent referrals are seen within 48 hours and current routine waiting times are 2 weeks.</p>
<p><strong>Occupational Therapy</strong> – focuses on rehabilitation through function that is task based e.g. facilitating a person’s discharge from hospital by assessing a patient’s ability to manage activities of daily living.  There is also an out patient service for Consultant and GP referred patients who have problems with using their upper limb, usually hand function.  All Occupational Therapists are HPC and British Association of Occupational Therapist registered.  Staff undertake  specialist training to provide the most up to date evidence based treatment e.g. Post operative hand surgery, simulated work based assessments.  Splints and braces can be provided to aid function if appropriate.  </p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
